    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A single-page, vertical-scrolling application with a fixed top navigation bar. The structure is thematic, guiding the user from foundational concepts ('Marketing 101') to career exploration ('Marketing Career Paths') then to practical application ('The Brand Toolkit', 'Putting it into Practice') and strategic thinking ('Strategy in Action'). This non-linear but guided flow is more engaging than a simple presentation, allowing users to explore sections at their own pace via scrolling or the nav bar. Interactive elements like tabs and clickable cards are used to break down information and encourage user engagement, making the content more digestible for a college-aged audience. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Report Info: 'What is a brand?', 'What is NOT a brand?', 'What dilutes a brand?'. Goal: Inform/Engage. Viz/Method: Interactive flip cards. Interaction: Click to reveal text. Justification: More dynamic and memorable than static text. Library: HTML/CSS/JS.
        - Report Info: 'Specific examples that dilute a brand'. Goal: Inform/Engedage. Viz/Method: Interactive flip card. Interaction: Click to reveal text. Justification: Provides concrete examples to reinforce understanding of brand dilution. Library: HTML/CSS/JS.
        - Report Info: 'Marketing is 10% creative, 90% strategic'. Goal: Compare/Inform. Viz/Method: Donut Chart. Interaction: Hover tooltips, automatic fluctuation. Justification: Provides immediate visual impact for a key conceptual ratio and demonstrates its dynamic nature. Library: Chart.js.
        - Report Info: 'Marketing Career Paths'. Goal: Inform/Organize. Viz/Method: Grid of descriptive cards. Interaction: Static information. Justification: Clearly presents diverse roles in an easy-to-digest format. Library: HTML/CSS.
        - Report Info: Design, Editorial, Social Media Guides, Dominican Brand Platform. Goal: Organize/Inform. Viz/Method: Tabbed interface. Interaction: Click tabs to switch content. Justification: Condenses large amounts of text into a manageable, user-controlled component, preventing information overload. Library: HTML/JS.
        - Report Info: Storyboard for "Day in the Life" Reel. Goal: Organize/Illustrate Process. Viz/Method: Interactive card-based storyboard. Interaction: Next/Previous buttons to navigate scenes. Justification: Actively demonstrates the concept of storyboarding in a step-by-step, interactive format. Library: HTML/JS.
        - Report Info: Importance of KPIs. Goal: Inform/Visualize. Viz/Method: Bar Chart. Interaction: Hover tooltips. Justification: Makes the abstract concept of performance metrics tangible and easier to understand through a simple visual comparison. Library: Chart.js.
    -->
