        <section id="section-4" class="py-20">
            <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
                <div class="text-center mb-12">
                    <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-[#008eb3]">Putting it into Practice</h2>
                    <p class="mt-3 text-lg text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">Theory is great, but application is what matters. This section explores real-world scenarios you'll encounter as a student leader, from promoting your club's events to representing the school externally. Understanding these distinctions is key to being an effective brand ambassador.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
                    <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg p-8">
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-center text-[#008eb3]">Internal Events</h3>
                        <p class="text-center text-gray-500 mb-4">(e.g., Club Activities)</p>
                        <div class="text-center text-5xl mb-4">🎨</div>
                        <h4 class="font-semibold text-lg text-[#008eb3]">More Creative Freedom</h4>
                        <p class="mt-2 text-gray-600">You can be more playful and experimental. Use colors and fonts that represent your club's unique identity. The goal is to be eye-catching and tailored to your specific audience.</p>
                        <h4 class="font-semibold text-lg text-[#008eb3] mt-4">Subtle Brand Connection</h4>
                        <p class="mt-2 text-gray-600">While you have liberty, you should still subtly incorporate the school's brand. Use an official logo where appropriate and always maintain a level of professionalism.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg p-8">
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-center text-[#008eb3]">External Events</h3>
                        <p class="text-center text-gray-500 mb-4">(e.g., Conferences)</p>
